           <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
         {% endfor %}</ul>
 
+    Like the :func:`~jinja-filters.sort` filter, sorting and grouping is
+    case-insensitive by default. The ``key`` for each group is the value
+    of the first item in that group, keeping its original case. This can
+    be disabled by passing ``case_sensitive=True``.
+
+    You can also get the number of items in each group by passing
+    ``with_counts=True``, which yields ``(grouper, list, count)``
+    3-tuples instead.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items, count in users|groupby("city", with_counts=true) %}
+          <li>{{ city }} ({{ count }})</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``case_sensitive`` and ``with_counts`` parameters.
+        Sorting and grouping is now case-insensitive by default, matching
+        the ``sort`` filter.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
